Write narratives that:
a. Include a beginning;
b. Include events in order;
c. Use temporal words to signal event order (e.g., first, next, next,
then);
d. Provide details to describe actions, thoughts, and/or feelings;
e. Provide a middle; and
f. Provide an ending. (E)

